name: DAMMIT IM MAD
description: Another example of the hetero-palindrome, this time we have DAMMITIMAD, which when we pull the words apart reads, Dammit, I'm mad. This one is a little bit of a stretch as, dammit, really isn't a word per se, as much as it is slang. Technically, it should be "damn it", but I'll allow it because...well...I like it. I normally stick by the rules of grammar, spelling, punctuation, etc., but sometimes I feel frisky and live on the edge. This doesn't happen often so relish in the abstraction from minimalist abstraction of semantic truth.
